comments: Valanciunas (NOP) establishes himself in Edwards' (MIN) path and does not deliver contact.
Gobert (MIN) brings his hands toward Murphy III (NOP), and marginal contact occurs as Gobert releases away to roll to the basket.
Gobert (MIN) grazes Williamson (NOP) during his driving shot attempt, and the contact is marginal.
Gobert (MIN) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Williamson (NOP) and marginal contact occurs as Williamson attempts to move under the pick.
Valanciunas (NOP) is drawn into the air on the pump fake toward McDaniels (MIN) when arm and body contact occurs, affecting the shot attempt.

As Williamson (NOP) jumps toward the basket during his normal shooting motion, incidental contact occurs with Gobert (MIN), who is moving alongside him. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed incidental when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Williamson (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from McDaniels (MIN) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Williamson's (NOP) first two initial touches to the ball are not deemed to be controlled dribbles. He then legally gathers the ball with two hands and takes a controlled dribble toward the basket.
Hayes (NOP) places a resting forearm on Edwards' (MIN) side, and marginal contact occurs during his drive.
Hayes' (NOP) hand brushes Edwards' (MIN) left arm as he finishes the dunk attempt.
Hayes (NOP) establishes himself as he firms up over his left leg in Edwards' (MIN) path when marginal contact occurs on the pick.
Gobert (MIN) initiates contact with Williamson's (NOP) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
A delay of game warning is assessed to Minnesota.
Daniels (NOP) is moving alongside Edwards' (MIN) path as marginal body contact occurs when they come together during the drive.
Daniels (NOP) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) jump shot attempt.
